message: It is not clear that the Glasgow City Police were the first police force.  Several cities had acts of parliament that allowed them to create 'police'.  Also worth noting that definition of a police force at this stage is vague - the Glasgow force were responsible for a much wider list of responsibilities than would be recognised today.  Therefore intro has not named any force as first and made neutral.  Also County Police Act not first.  Muncipal Corp Act 1835 introduced borough police...
